	<div class="unit-reflection">
	One of the new skills I worked on for a long time in the Foundation Writing Program is supporting my arguments with various proper evidence. When I wrote the most challenging genre I met in the Foundation Writing Program, literature review, I learned how to select appropriate evidence and use them to support my argument. What’s more, I learned different techniques to integrate this evidence to my paragraphs, like summary of single source and synthesis evidence from different sources, as well as usage of integral and non-integral citations. This skill is one of the most important and useful skills I practiced, because evidence supported argument is widely used in all sorts of writings, including academic writing, business writing, and technical writing, which are very common types of writings I will meet in workplaces.
